== Japanese content ==
'''Kusumoto Shrine''' (くすもとじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Yao|Q490872|qid=Q490872|1=Yao, Osaka}}, {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|qid=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}. It is a shikinaisha recorded in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyocho|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} as "Kusumoto Shrine, three seats, Kuwa-yuki, Shiki District, Kawachi Province," and today it is enshrined at three locations in Yao: Kinomoto (former {{ill|lt=Tanboku District|Q11368489|qid=Q11368489|1=Tanboku district}}), Kita-Kinomoto, and Minami-Kinomoto (former {{ill|lt=Shiki District|Q11491125|qid=Q11491125|1=Shiki district}}).

=== Overview ===
Its founding date is unknown, but it is thought to date back to before the Kofun period. The enshrined deity was originally regarded as {{ill|lt=kodama|Q1515938|qid=Q1515938|1=Kodama (spirit)}} (tree spirit), and later identified with {{ill|lt=Futsu-no-Mitama|Q11059754|qid=Q11059754|lt=Futsu Omikami|1=Futsu-no-mitama}} and {{ill|lt=Nigihayahi|Q10949054|qid=Q10949054|lt=Nigihayahi-no-Mikoto|1=Nigihayahi}}. Because this area was former territory of the {{ill|lt=Mononobe clan|Q1755836|qid=Q1755836|1=Mononobe clan}}, it is thought that deities revered by {{ill|lt=Mononobe no Moriya|Q2424736|qid=Q2424736|1=Mononobe no Moriya}} as guardian gods were brought here in the reign of Emperor Yomei.

Originally there were three seats in Kimoto village, but when Kita-Kimoto split off and later Minami-Kimoto split off, one seat each was divided to those villages.

=== Kinomoto ===
{{神社
|名称=Kusumoto Shrine
|画像=[[File:Kusumoto-jinja (Kinomoto, Yao), keidai.jpg|250px]]<br />Kusumoto Shrine (Kinomoto) precincts
|所在地= {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|qid=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Yao|Q490872|qid=Q490872|1=Yao, Osaka}}Kinomoto 1-59
|位置={{ウィキ座標2段度分秒|34|36|4|N|135|35|14|E|}}
|祭神=Kodama (also called Futsu Omikami)
|創建=Unknown
|社格={{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} (small)
|例祭=Kinomoto: July 15 and October 9<br />Minami-Kinomoto: October 9-10
|神事=
|本殿=
|地図= {{Location map|Japan Osaka|label=Kusumoto Shrine|coordinates=
{{coord2|34|36|4|N|135|35|14|E|}}|position=bottom|width=200|mark=Shinto torii icon vermillion.svg|marksize=15|float=center|caption=}}
{{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=12|marker=religious-shinto|frame-align=center|frame-width=200|coord={{coord|34|36|4|N|135|35|14|E}}}}
}}
It is enshrined in the old Kimoto settlement of Kinomoto 1-chome. From the Minami-Kinomoto Kusumoto Shrine, go one intersection south and two intersections west.
