File:Kusumoto-jinja (Kinomoto, Yao), torii.jpg|Torii
</gallery>
{{-}}

=== Kita-Kinomoto ===
{{神社
|名称=Kusumoto Shrine
|画像=[[File:Kusumoto-jinja (Kita-kinomoto, Yao), haiden.jpg|250px]]<br />Kusumoto Shrine (Kita-Kinomoto) worship hall
|所在地 = {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|qid=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Yao|Q490872|qid=Q490872|1=Yao, Osaka}}Kita-Kinomoto 5-73
|位置={{ウィキ座標2段度分秒|34|36|32|N|135|35|21|E|}}
|祭神=Kodama (also called Futsu Omikami)
|創建=Unknown
|社格={{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} (small)
|例祭=Kinomoto: July 15 and October 9<br />Minami-Kinomoto: October 9-10
|神事=
|本殿=
|地図= {{Location map|Japan Osaka|label=Kusumoto Shrine|coordinates=
{{coord2|34|36|32|N|135|35|21|E|}}|position=bottom|width=200|mark=Shinto torii icon vermillion.svg|marksize=15|float=center|caption=}}
{{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=12|marker=religious-shinto|frame-align=center|frame-width=200|coord={{coord|34|36|32|N|135|35|21|E}}}}
}}
It is on the west side along the former Osaka Chuo Kanjo Line (former Yao-Fujiidera Line). In the precincts is a pond about 3 meters in diameter said to be where {{ill|lt=Mononobe no Moriya|Q2424736|qid=Q2424736|1=Mononobe no Moriya}}'s head was washed. There is a children's park in the center of the grounds, with a small shrine building at the back. Among the three shrines, this one is the smallest in scale.
<gallery>
File:Kusumoto-jinja (Kita-kinomoto, Yao), honden.jpg|Main hall
File:Kusumoto-jinja (Kita-kinomoto, Yao), ike.jpg|Pond said to be where Moriya's head was washed
File:Kusumoto-jinja (Kita-kinomoto, Yao), torii.jpg|Torii
</gallery>
{{-}}

=== Minami-Kinomoto ===
{{神社
|名称=Kusumoto Shrine
|画像=[[File:Kusumoto-jinja (Minami-kinomoto, Yao), keidai.jpg|250px]]<br />Kusumoto Shrine (Minami-Kinomoto) precincts
|所在地 = {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|qid=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Yao|Q490872|qid=Q490872|1=Yao, Osaka}}Minami-Kinomoto 7-33
|位置={{ウィキ座標2段度分秒|34|36|5|N|135|35|21|E|}}
|祭神=Kodama (also called Futsu Omikami)
|創建=Unknown
|社格={{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} (small)
|例祭=Kinomoto: July 15 and October 9<br />Minami-Kinomoto: October 9-10
|神事=
|本殿=
|地図= {{Location map|Japan Osaka|label=Kusumoto Shrine|coordinates=
{{coord2|34|36|5|N|135|35|21|E|}}|position=bottom|width=200|mark=Shinto torii icon vermillion.svg|marksize=15|float=center|caption=}}
{{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|zoom=12|marker=religious-shinto|frame-align=center|frame-width=200|coord={{coord|34|36|5|N|135|35|21|E}}}}
}}
It is on the west side along the city road (former Yao-Fujiidera Line) a little south of the Kinomoto intersection on the old Osaka Chuo Kanjo Line. The shrine buildings are on the north side of the grounds. On the south side is '''Nichira-ji''', a {{ill|lt=Buddhist|Q748|qid=Q748|1=Buddhism}} {{ill|lt=temple|Q5393308|qid=Q5393308|1=Buddhist temple}} of the Obaku school; its principal image is {{ill|lt=Yakushi Nyorai|Q854773|qid=Q854773|1=Bhaisajyaguru}}. It is said that {{ill|lt=Emperor Bidatsu|Q316637|qid=Q316637|1=Emperor Bidatsu}} granted this land to {{ill|lt=Nichira|Q11510262|qid=Q11510262|1=Nichira}}, who had been called back from {{ill|lt=Baekje|Q28428|qid=Q28428|1=Paekche}}, and Nichira built a temple here and enshrined a Yakushi Nyorai image.
<gallery>
File:Kusumoto-jinja (Minami-kinomoto, Yao), honden.jpg|Main hall
File:Kusumoto-jinja (Minami-kinomoto, Yao), haiden.jpg|Worship hall
File:Kusumoto-jinja (Minami-kinomoto, Yao), dou.jpg|Nichira-ji main hall
File:Kusumoto-jinja (Minami-kinomoto, Yao), torii.jpg|Torii
</gallery>
{{-}}

